<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-03-21T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-03-21T20:00:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163/116: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-22T09:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                                        1927—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 22—1:33
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>235. My 224, March 16, 6 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d254fn8">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from Chungking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“March 19, 5 p.m. Excluding Batang there remain in Szechuan 30
                                    Americans located as follows: Yachow, 1 woman and 1 man;
                                    Chengtu, 8 women, 1 baby and 7 men; Chungking, 11 men; Wanhsien,
                                    1 man.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>